{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "hrk-e2e-deterministic-full-v1",
    "name": "HRK E2E Deterministic Full",
    "description": "Deterministyczny scenariusz E2E (Setup -> Verify -> Cleanup) obejmujący pełny łańcuch CRM: customer, contacts, services, contracts, contract-services, valorizations, customer-rates, notes, activity-log.\n\n## RBAC/ABAC (ALF-60)\nKolekcja używa collection-level `Authorization: Bearer {{bearerToken}}`. Token jest ustawiany w requeście `01 - Login` (token = login, MVP). Endpoint logowania jest jedynym wyjątkiem (auth: noauth).\n\nDeterministyczny user (`testUserLogin`) musi mieć rolę `admin` aby request `03 - Create Company` (admin-only) zadziałał — w razie 403 wykonaj `99a - [Bootstrap] Grant Admin Role`.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      { "key": "token", "value": "{{bearerToken}}", "type": "string" }
    ]
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Collection-level prerequest: deterministic per-run defaults.",
          "// Each Run Collection regenerates testRunId so unique constraints (nip, ckk) never collide.",
          "function ensure(key, fallback) {",
          "    var v = pm.collectionVariables.get(key);",
          "    if (!v || v === '' || v === null) { pm.collectionVariables.set(key, fallback); }",
          "}",
          "ensure('testUserLogin', 'mateusz');",
          "ensure('bearerToken', pm.collectionVariables.get('testUserLogin'));",
          "// Always refresh testRunId so each collection run is unique.",
          "var rid = String(Date.now());",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('testRunId', rid);",
          "// 6-char numeric suffix that fits ckk (max_length=10) when prefixed with 'E2E-'.",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('shortRunId', rid.slice(-6));",
          "// 10-digit suffix for nip / billing_nip (max_length=15).",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('nipSuffix', (rid + '0000000000').slice(0, 10));"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "01 - Login",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Login OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
              "const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('userId', jsonData.id);",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('bearerToken', jsonData.login);",
              "console.log('Bearer token =', jsonData.login);"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/login/{{testUserLogin}}",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["auth", "login", "{{testUserLogin}}"]
        },
        "description": "Loguje użytkownika E2E. Po requeście `bearerToken = login` i wszystkie kolejne requesty używają nagłówka `Authorization: Bearer {{bearerToken}}` (collection-level)."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "01b - [Bootstrap] First Admin",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "if (pm.response.code === 404) {",
              "    console.error('404 → backend nie ma jeszcze /access/* routes. RESTART backendu (make run / docker-compose restart api) i puść kolekcję ponownie.');",
              "}",
              "pm.test('Bootstrap accepted (200) or locked (403)', function () {",
              "    pm.expect([200, 403]).to.include(pm.response.code);",
              "});",
              "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
              "    var roles = pm.response.json().roles || [];",
              "    pm.test('User now has admin role', function () { pm.expect(roles).to.include('admin'); });",
              "} else if (pm.response.code === 403) {",
              "    console.warn('Bootstrap locked — another user is already admin. Either log in as that admin or assign role through PUT /access/users/{id}/roles.');",
              "}"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/access/bootstrap-first-admin",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["access", "bootstrap-first-admin"]
        },
        "description": "Idempotentny self-bootstrap pierwszego admina. \n\n- 200: `testUserLogin` jest jedynym/pierwszym adminem – mamy go.\n- 200 (już admin): no-op, zwraca aktualne assignments.\n- 403: w bazie jest już *inny* admin – musisz zalogować się jako on i nadać rolę przez PUT /access/users/{id}/roles."
      }
    },
